The **Save As** dialog cannot do this because prompting to overwrite is hard-coded as `TRUE` in the [GTK source file][1]:

``` c
gtk_file_chooser_set_do_overwrite_confirmation(GTK_FILE_CHOOSER (chooser), TRUE);
```

[JDK-8299969][2] was logged against this issue, and will need to be resolved before the overwrite prompt can be ignored.

Using the **Open** dialog is a workaround, although it has drawbacks.

For [KeenWrite](https://github.com/DaveJarvis/keenwrite), I opted to have a hot-key that bypasses the **Save As** dialog altogether by repeating the previous export action. This can be accomplished by creating a `javafx.concurrent.Service` that is able to re-run a `javafx.concurrent.Task`, such as:

``` java
final var service = new Service&lt;Path&gt;() {
  @Override
  protected Task&lt;Path&gt; createTask() {
    final var task = new Task&lt;Path&gt;() {
      @Override
      protected Path call() throws Exception {
        // Do the work that Save As would do.
      }
    };

    // Handle the success functionality.
    task.setOnSucceeded( this::successs );

    // Handle the failure functionality.
    task.setOnFailed( this::failure );

    return task;
  }
};
```

In this way, if **Save As** is a feature users may do quite often, it can be replaced with a &quot;silent&quot; version that doesn&#39;t prompt with any dialogs. Except for the first time, which creates the initial action that will be re-run for subsequent &quot;silent&quot; executions.

  [1]: https://github.com/openjdk/jfx/blob/bca1bfc5e3b04293c13417fd923d99864cdd9147/modules/javafx.graphics/src/main/native-glass/gtk/GlassCommonDialogs.cpp#L125
  [2]: https://bugs.java.com/bugdatabase/view_bug.do?bug_id=JDK-8299969

