You can write your own [FilterOutputStream][1]:

_This class is the superclass of all classes that filter output streams. These streams sit on top of an already existing output stream (the underlying output stream) which it uses as its basic sink of data, but possibly transforming the data along the way or providing additional functionality._

        BufferedOutputStream buffer = new BufferedOutputStream(super.getOutputStream());
        
